"xv6-riscv" is a re-implementation of Dennis Ritchie's and Ken Thompson's Unix
Version 6 implemented for a modern RISC-V multiprocessor using ANSI C.

On top of refactoring, this repository contains the following additions:
- Kernel threads
- Exceptions for null pointer dereferences
- Lottery scheduler for processes
- System call tracing
- New system calls: alarm, read counts, getpinfo, settickets (for scheduler)
- Changed the protection bits of parts of the page table to be read-only